## THIRD-PARTY TECHNOLOGIES

This Software incorporates or implements various signal processing, coding, and communication technologies. These technologies, algorithms, and methods may be covered by patents, copyrights, or other intellectual property rights held by their respective owners.

**Technologies implemented include but are not limited to:**
- LDPC (Low-Density Parity-Check) codes based on IEEE 802.11n specifications
- OFDM (Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing)
- Zadoff-Chu sequences
- Chirp spread spectrum synchronization
- HARQ (Hybrid Automatic Repeat Request) with chase combining
- Various modulation schemes (DPSK, QAM, etc.)

**Third-party libraries included:**
- Dear ImGui (MIT License) - See `thirdparty/imgui/LICENSE.txt`
- miniz (Public Domain) - See `thirdparty/miniz/`
- SDL2 (zlib License) - System dependency
- FFTW3 (GPL or commercial) - System dependency

See `LICENSE_THIRDPARTY.md` for additional third-party attribution.

